<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-06T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-06T09:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5 Submarines/30½: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-06T14:00:00+00:00">October 6,
                                    1936—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 6—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>462. My despatch No. 2526 September 22, 1936.<note n="7" xml:id="d151fn7">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office advises that His Majesty’s
                            Embassy at Rome has been informed by the Italian Government that it
                            proposes to ratify part IV of the London Naval Treaty 1930 early in
                            October. The Foreign Office therefore desires to effect arrangements for
                            early signature of the submarine protocol and has prepared the text of
                            the procès-verbal which is in conformity with that previously
                            transmitted to the Department. Am I authorized to sign and in that case
                            when may I expect to receive my full power?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>